## Phase 3: Database & Data Access (Weeks 21–28)

### Topics to Cover

**3.1 — Entity Framework Core (Primary ORM)**
- Code-First approach: entities, DbContext, migrations
- Fluent API vs Data Annotations for configuration
- Relationships: one-to-one, one-to-many, many-to-many
- Querying: eager loading (`Include`), explicit loading, lazy loading
- Change tracking, `AsNoTracking()`
- Raw SQL queries and interpolated queries
- Performance: query optimization, N+1 problem, compiled queries
- Migrations in production: strategies for safe schema changes

**3.2 — Dapper (Lightweight Alternative)**
- When to use Dapper vs EF Core
- Basic CRUD with Dapper
- Multi-mapping, stored procedures
- Performance comparison with EF Core

**3.3 — SQL Server Deep Dive**
- Indexing strategies (clustered, non-clustered, covering indexes)
- Query execution plans
- Stored procedures, views, CTEs
- Transactions and isolation levels
- Connection pooling

**3.4 — NoSQL Basics**
- Redis for caching (StackExchange.Redis)
- MongoDB basics with .NET driver (optional but good to know)

### How to Practice
- Take your Phase 2 API project and add a proper database layer
- Write complex queries: reports with joins, aggregations, CTEs
- Profile your EF Core queries — identify and fix N+1 problems
- Set up Redis caching for frequently accessed data

