## Phase 4: Architecture & Design Patterns (Weeks 29–40)

This is what separates mid-level from senior. Companies like Microsoft and Goldman Sachs will ask architecture questions.

### Topics to Cover

**4.1 — SOLID Principles (Know These Cold)**
- Single Responsibility, Open/Closed, Liskov Substitution, Interface Segregation, Dependency Inversion
- Real C# examples for each, not just theory

**4.2 — Design Patterns in C#**
- Creational: Factory, Abstract Factory, Builder, Singleton
- Structural: Adapter, Decorator, Facade, Proxy
- Behavioral: Strategy, Observer, Command, Chain of Responsibility, Mediator
- Repository pattern and Unit of Work

**4.3 — Clean Architecture**
- Domain layer, Application layer, Infrastructure layer, Presentation layer
- Dependency rule: inner layers don't reference outer layers
- CQRS (Command Query Responsibility Segregation) with MediatR
- Domain-Driven Design (DDD) basics: Entities, Value Objects, Aggregates, Domain Events

**4.4 — Modular Monolith**
- Module boundaries and communication
- When monolith vs microservices (spoiler: monolith is usually right for teams < 10)
- Vertical slice architecture

